          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "No. The United States does not publish systematic federal crime statistics disaggregated by immigration status or nativity. The FBI's Uniform Crime Reporting (UCR) / NIBRS database records arrests by age, sex, and race, but immigration status is not collected as a variable. The Bureau of Justice Statistics does not publish a routine report comparing crime rates of native-born vs. foreign-born populations at the national level."
        }
